This repository uses the **Jelly** language to write Apple Shortcuts compiled with the open-source [`jelly` CLI](https://github.com/OpenJelly/Open-Jellycore).

## Source of Truth

The complete syntax rules, coding standards, and agent workflow guidelines are in:

**`.agent/rules/jelly-syntax.md`**

Read that file before writing or editing any `.jelly` file in this repository.

## Quick Reference

- `import Shortcuts` must be line 1 — no exceptions
- `#Color` and `#Icon` metadata required on every script
- Nil-check `ShortcutInput` immediately after metadata if the shortcut takes input
- No variables in `case` labels — hardcoded string literals only
- Use `make deploy FILE=<path>` to compile, sign, and open a shortcut

## Agent Skills

All reusable agent workflows (scaffold, compile, debug, deploy, import) are in `.agent/skills/`. See `AGENTS.md` for the full map.
